headlines.description: — Jakob Poeltl scored 30 points, Pascal Siakam had 26 and the Toronto Raptors beat the Orlando Magic 123-113 on Tuesday night for their fifth win in six games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poeltl scores 30, Siakam has 26, Raptors beat Magic 123-113

headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday demonstrated just why he’s heading to the All-Star Game for the first time in a decade.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks edge Celtics 131-125 in OT for 11th straight win

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 32 points, Deandre Ayton had 29 points and 11 rebounds, and the Phoenix Suns beat the Sacramento Kings 120-109 on Tuesday night with superstar acquisition Kevin Durant watching from the bench.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns top Kings 120-109 with Durant watching from bench

events.name: Golden State Warriors at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Clippers have 22 games remaining to integrate their trade deadline acquisitions. They didn't waste any time.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard's 33 points lead Clippers over Warriors, 134-124

events.name: Washington Wizards at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma returned from an ankle sprain and scored 33 points, making six 3-pointers, to lead the Washington Wizards to a 126-101 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma returns from injury and Wizards top Blazers 126-101
